[While this disease does tend to resemble foot and mouth disease (FMD), it must be remembered that FMD does not occur in horses.

Nevertheless, out of caution, it is likely that other states will slam their doors shut regarding animals from Wyoming. This is expected. However, and fortunately, most animals heal within approximately 3 weeks.

If you are planning on moving animals out of Wyoming, please check with the state of destination for regulations. - Mod.TG

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3698707,251.]
